benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails - Retrieve an account emails

covered: Valid Request: TC01 covers successful retrieval of emails for an existing account with data (200, JSON array of AccountEmail objects)
Empty Response: TC02 covers scenario where an account has no emails (200, empty array)
Input Validation / Parameter Handling: TC03 covers invalid accountId format (400) and TC04 covers non-existent but valid-format accountId returning an empty array (200)
Query Parameter Handling: TC07 covers extra parameters being ignored by the API (200, proper response)
Error Handling: TC06 covers service unavailability with 503
Performance/Scale: TC08 covers handling of a very large number of emails and response timing
Security: TC10 (SQL injection) and TC11 (XSS) test input sanitization and error handling
Unicode/Character Handling: TC12 ensures emails with special/unicode characters are returned correctly
Concurrency/Load: TC13 tests concurrent requests for the same account
Backward Compatibility: TC14 ensures compatibility with legacy clients
Accessibility/Documentation: TC15 ensures error messages are accessible and clear
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets (page size, page tokens, next/prev links)
Rate Limiting: No tests cover rate limiting/throttling (e.g., bursty traffic or quotas)
Caching Behavior: No tests verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching behavior
Explicit risk-related security tests beyond basic input sanitization: no targeted tests for complex attack vectors beyond TC10/TC11
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to validate paging behavior and boundaries (e.g., pageSize, page, totalPages)
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under high request volume
Add caching header tests (ETag, Cache-Control) and verify caching behavior
Expand security test coverage with additional edge-case inputs and header-based protections
Document and validate error payload schemas for consistent machine-readable error responses
